title: 820-3332-A A1398
message:

 3v3s5_en =3.4V

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message: pp3v3_s5 is present pp3v3_sus is not.

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message: Check S5_PWRGD, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PM_SLP_SUS_L and all RTC signals.

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message:
3.38 s5_pwrgd
3.41 pm_dsw_pwrgd
3.33 pm_slp_sus_l
3.3 rtc_reset_l
5mV ppvout_g3_pch
3.3 ppvrtc_g3h
465mV sysclk_clk32k_rtc

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message: I did just try to plug in the bord again, and it’s constantly boot looping with the battery connected. The fans spin and goes from 15mA to 1Amp over and over.  This is without the side IO board plugged in. I don't have another known good battery to test, could it just be the battery?

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message:
"all RTC signals"
Read the "How To collection" thread, for the future.
If board tries to start now, RTC signals should be good however.

You had missing 3V3_SUS at U7930 before; can you check it again now?

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message:
Sorry, I just went in board view and measured anything that had RTC in it.
3v3sus is present when it tries to turn on.

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message:
All mentioned signals are steady high?
Be sure to test with original 85W Magsafe charger.

title: 820-3332-A A1398
message: It was the charger.. Thank you so much for your help, I feel so dumb lol.
